Package: libsixsv1
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: 6SV2.1 atmospheric correction library
 A C11 port of the 6SV2.1 (Second Simulation of the Satellite Signal in
 the Solar Spectrum) radiative transfer model for operational atmospheric
 correction of multispectral and hyperspectral remote sensing imagery.
 .
 Features: DISCOM discrete-ordinate solver; 3-D [AOD × H₂O × λ] LUT;
 per-pixel Lambertian and BRDF-coupled inversion; H₂O, AOD, O₃ and
 surface-pressure retrievals; MAIAC AOD regularisation; Hapke, RPV and
 Ross-Li BRDF models; NBAR, MCD43 disaggregation; adjacency, terrain
 and uncertainty propagation; OpenMP parallelism.

Package: libsixsv-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libsixsv1 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: 6SV2.1 atmospheric correction library — development files
 Development headers and linker stub for libsixsv.
 .
 Install this package to build C or C++ programs that call into lib6sv.
 The public API is exposed through the headers in /usr/include/sixsv/:
 atcorr.h, brdf.h, retrieve.h, spatial.h, terrain.h, adjacency.h,
 uncertainty.h, spectral_brdf.h, oe_invert.h.
